HEADWORD: Cotarnine
<hw>Co*tar"nine</hw> <pr>(k?-t?r"n?n ⟦or⟧ -n?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F., fr. <ets>narcotine</ets>, by transposition of letters.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A white, crystalline substance,
<chform>C12H13NO3</chform>, obtained as a product of the decomposition
of narcotine. It has weak basic properties, and is usually regarded as
an alkaloid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cote</ent>⟦br⟧
